replies.body:
As a fellow Zac top main, I am sorely disappointed in Riot's decision to uproot this champion to garbage status. Even if they left his Q alone and changed his ult to what it is he'd at least still be a viable champion in the game. But now, with this Q change, he lost his biggest and best attribute, AOE wave clear and champion poke. It was so easy to position yourself to target enemy champions inside the lane while they were trying to farm, which is what made Zac so hard to deal with in the top lane. Now, you cant even target an enemy champion unless they are in front of the minions or there is no wave period. Now the only possibility is to max W first, which could work, but puts him within arms reach every time.

Riot did to Zac what they attempted with Skarner and force him solely in the Jungle. We can even have fun in mid lane AP anymore with this change because his Q will never even hit the enemy. Makes me sad losing another main. 

